div.p:
Choreographs processing of the
request to the appropriate subsystem.

A request can either be sent immediately
to the histogram service or sent to the
queue service and processed asynchronously.

div.p: Manages asynchronous processing of deferred requests. An identifier is created for each request, the request data is passed on to the store service, then the ID is returned and ultimately passed on to the user.
Every second, the service checks the queue for un-completed requests, retrieves information from the store esrvice on the request, then passes the request back to core for immediate processing.
